# Code Standards

- `<name>.go`: testable business logic.
- `<name>_init.go`: constructors, OS/filesystem setup, panic-recovery wrappers, schema init. Excluded from coverage.
- No business logic in `*_init.go`.
- Put `// nocov` on a line inside the uncovered block, and only for paths that truly cannot be tested.
- Unused parameters: remove them and update callers when you own the signature. When a shared `func`/interface forces an argument that only some implementations need, use `_` for that parameter (or omit the name: `func(string)`).
- Prefer dependency injection (interfaces) over concrete types.
- Source-package-specific structure lives in `datasources.mdc`.
